  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 55fc01baa0be7b54e8ef6801bfc93ce6, type: 3}
  m_Name: YourselfThree
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  PromptOneButtonDisplay: 0
  PromptTwoButtonDisplay: 0
  ButtonOneText: 
  ButtonTwoText: 
  NormalDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: "Shooting yourself midway into the game\u2026"
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Are you going to make another one of your comments?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Yes, but you're still choosing to listen.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: ...
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: One thing I enjoy about hosting this game is that I get to see truly
      different people than in other typical jobs.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I see traces of their remaining humanity, despite them looking, well,
      not human, through their words and my deductions.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Have you made connections with those people?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: From the second they sign the contract, I already know who they are,
      but when the game is over, they won't remember me. I will.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Some have left an impression on me, but everyone's story belongs to
      them, not me.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Because I'm with you, I know everything about you until this game ends.
      However, the same types of characters only come to play my game.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Broken people are my demographic. If everyone is hurting, why does your
      pain matter compared to theirs? It's a question that pops into my head when
      I hear my clients talking.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: 'You''re not unique because you feel pain. '
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Ha, you're right about that. Everyone suffers in their own way and some
      hide it better than others.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: 'Ugh, everything is dull, mundane, the same. '
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: People don't change. People don't need to be explicit to make you question
      your worth. People are sly snakes that secretly spew poison, hiding their fangs
      and pretending to seem gentle.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: 'Choices are meaningless because something or someone else will want
      to make the choices for you or heavily influence them. Why? They don''t trust.
      If they don''t trust me, then I''m not going to trust you either. '
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Individuality is a myth once you belong to a system of pain.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: How can you be you if others don't allow you to be? Why try then? You
      keep trying. Things keep crumbling, then you give up because you'll never be
      allowed to be you.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Family, friends, work, all have an idea of who you are to them. But
      those ideas are all different. They all shove their expectations under the
      label of 'care', then even caring eventually becomes a lie.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: So what does that make you?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: You belong to them, not to yourself.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: Ahaha, you're really funny. Really funny...
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They grasp their arm. The arm is horribly torn up. Parts of their flesh
      are exposed and red from the brute force of wool being ripped off.
  - CharacterTitle: 0
    Message: They tear a larger chunk of wool than they intended higher up their
      arm and hand the clump over.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I'll shuffle a new round now.
  - CharacterTitle: 3
    Message: 'I just want this over with so I can stop listening to you. '
  ButtonOneDialogue: []
  ButtonTwoDialogue: []
